Don ' t sleep forever in ` dumpapp crash throw ` 
 Wait on the crash thread instead , which will appropriately block the 
 command line until the crash is acknowledged by Android and takes down 
 the process . Tested this with : 
 former = Thread . getDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler ( ) ; 
 Thread . setDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler ( ( . . . ) - > { 
 Thread . sleep ( 5000 ) ; 
 former . uncaughtException ( . . . ) ; 
 } ) ; 
 This caused ` dumpapp crash throw ` to hang for 5 seconds before the 
 process crashed and then the control was returned to the command line as 
 expected . 
 Separately , not invoking former . uncaughtException caused the process to 
 continue running , and ` dumpapp crash throw ` returns immediately ( as 
 it should even if counter intuitively ) .

